name: INRIX x AWS Hackathon • 1st Place
description: Developed a web application that uses INRIX's traffic data to predict car accidents and display them on a heat map. Built with React, Node.js, and AWS.

name: Jones Idea Challenge • 3rd Place
description: Our proposal revolved around designing an app that integrates AI into Melissa Reaves' platform, reducing the friction in connecting coaches to customers and creating an online space for customers to learn the "Mind Movie Method."

name: Possible • Fellowship Position
description: Was 1 of just 40 students to be nominated by faculty and accepted into the SeattleU x Santa Clara Career Accelerator powered by Possible, a career development program for the tech industry.
